<item>
            <title>[LU-18690] false failure in sanity-quota/79</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18690</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
== sanity-quota test 79: access to non-existed dt-pool/info doesn&apos;t cause a panic ========================================================== 23:44:36 (1736639076)
/tmp/f79.sanity-quota
Creating &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; pool qpool1
Pool lustre.qpool1 created
 sanity-quota test_79: @@@@@@ FAIL: test_79 failed with 2 
  Trace dump:
  = ./../tests/test-framework.sh:7232:error()
  = ./../tests/test-framework.sh:7605:run_one()
  = ./../tests/test-framework.sh:7668:run_one_logged()
  = ./../tests/test-framework.sh:7486:run_test()
  = sanity-quota.sh:6001:main()
Dumping lctl log to /tmp/ltest-logs/sanity-quota.test_79.*.1736639078.log
Dumping logs only on local client.
Destroy the created pools: qpool1
lustre.qpool1
Pool lustre.qpool1 destroyed
test_79 returned 1
FAIL 79 (5s)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this is because the background &quot;rm -f $stopf&quot; can race with the foreground one and the test can return a result of the background rm.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
